<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC6FFD0FF29FC83BBD2CC8E" box="[136,1255,878,905]" pageId="21" pageNumber="242" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC6FFD0FF29FC83BBD2CC8E" blockId="21.[136,1255,878,905]" box="[136,1255,878,905]" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">
C10: 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC6FFD0FF67FC83BCE3CC8E" authority="Homma, Trans. Sapporo Nat. Hist. Soc." box="[198,982,878,905]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="21" pageNumber="242" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis-amblyolepis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FF67FC83BD24CC8F" bold="true" box="[198,529,878,905]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Puccinia caricis-amblyolepis</emphasis>
Homma, Trans. Sapporo Nat. Hist. Soc.
</taxonomicName>
15: 122, 1938. (
<figureCitation id="13512A00FFC6FFD0FB2FFC83BBEBCC8E" box="[1166,1246,878,904]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="22.[136,229,1128,1150]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,281,1103]" captionTargetId="figure-78@22.[151,1436,281,1103]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 13. Puccinia caricis-amblyolepis on Carex sp. A. Plants producing uredinia and telia on the leaf surface in the field. B. Vertical section of a uredinium. C. Urediniospores. D. Uredinia and telia on the lower leaf surface. E. Teliospores. F. Vertical section of a telium. Scale bars: B, C = 30 μm, E, F = 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6416795" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6416795/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC6FFD0FF29FC5BBD36CBAE" pageId="21" pageNumber="242" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC6FFD0FF29FC5BBD36CBAE" blockId="21.[136,1452,950,1733]" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FF29FC5BBE29CCD6" bold="true" box="[136,284,950,976]" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Description:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FE99FC5ABEF8CCD7" box="[312,461,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Spermogonia</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FDA9FC5ABD70CCD6" box="[520,581,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">aecia</emphasis>
not found. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FD6DFC5BBC05CCD6" box="[716,816,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Uredinia</emphasis>
hypophyllous, scattered, minute, brown to dark brown, covered by epidermis but eventually erumpent. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FD0AFC37BC62CCF2" box="[683,855,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Urediniospores</emphasis>
globose, subglobose or obovoid, 22.0–32.0 × 19.6– 25.5 µm (av. 27.0 × 22.5 µm); walls brown, echinulate, 1.1–1.6 µm (av. 1.3 µm), germ pores 2–3. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FB6FFC13BA30CB1E" box="[1230,1285,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Telia</emphasis>
hypophyllous, blackish brown, rounded to broadly elliptic, erumpent. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC6FFD0FCB5FBCFBCA6CB3A" box="[788,915,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="242">Teliospores</emphasis>
broadly clavate, ellipsoid, mostly truncate or rounded at apices, constricted at the septa, attenuate at the bases, 42.0–56.5 × 15.5–21.0 µm (av. 8.5 × 19.0 µm); walls brown, 0.8–1.0 µm (av. = 0.9 µm) thick at sides, 7.5–13.0 µm (av. 9.5 µm) at apices; pedicels persistent, hyaline, 12.5–29.5 µm (av. 19.0 µm) long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
